augroup base
  " Compute syntax highlighting from beginning of file. (By default, vim only
  " looks 200 lines back, which can make it highlight code incorrectly in some
  " long files.)
  autocmd BufEnter * :syntax sync fromstart
	autocmd CmdwinEnter * nnoremap <buffer> <CR> <CR>
	autocmd BufReadPost quickfix nnoremap <buffer> <CR> <CR>
	autocmd QuickFixCmdPost [^l]* nested cwindow
	autocmd CmdwinEnter * nnoremap <buffer> <CR> <CR>

  " example of how to prep :make for filetypes
  " either that or just have a `compile` script that selects on run?
	autocmd FileType rust setlocal makeprg=cargo\ build
augroup END

